column1: Duplexe Tchamba Bangou (born 10 July 1998) is a Cameroonian professional footballer who plays as a defender for the club Strømsgodset
Tchamba was a product of the TAD Sport Academy in Cameroon
column2: and moved to Strasbourg on 22 March 2017. He made his professional debut for Strasbourg in a 1–0 Coupe de France win over Grenoble Foot 38 on 16 January 2019.

column1: Tchamba represented Cameroon U20s at the 2017 Africa U-20 Cup of Nations
column2: and the Cameroon U23s in a set of friendlies.
